[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bloxwich amputee girl surprises doctors by skateboarding

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A seven-year-old girl who was born with a condition that meant she cannot use her legs has surprised doctors with her active life.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
9 January 2015 Last updated at 10:25 GMT
Rosie Davies from Bloxwich has a condition that means her spine was not attached to her pelvis.
Surgeons amputated her legs and used a bone to fuse her body together, in an attempt to make sure she could sit properly in a wheelchair.
But as BBC Midlands Today's Joanne Writtle reports, Rosie does not use a wheelchair - she goes to dance classes and even speeds around on a skateboard.
